-- Poland’s Innova, EBRD Buy Stake in Romanian EnergoBit, ZF Says
-- B y   A n d r a   T i m u
-- 2012-11-26T07:13:11Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-11-26/poland-s-innova-ebrd-buy-stake-in-romanian-energobit-zf-says.html
Innova Capital , a Poland-based
private equity fund, acquired a majority stake in EnergoBit ESCO
SA, a Romanian supplier of electricity equipment,  Ziarul
Financiar  reported.  The European Bank for Reconstruction and Development also
bought a minority stake in  EnergoBit , the Bucharest-based
newspaper said, citing Stefan Gadola and Ioan Socea, two of the
company’s founding shareholders. The value of the transaction
wasn’t disclosed, according to Ziarul Financiar.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andra Timu in Bucharest at 
 atimu@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
